<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,272,418]" box="[151,270,272,297]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis box="[151,270,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,272,418]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[544,697,312,337]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidentatus">
<emphasis box="[544,697,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">L. bidentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as demonstrated by cephalically-directed furculae) and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">L. viridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as demonstrated by similar genital structure and coloration pattern), but differs from the latter two by the characters listed in 
<tableCitation box="[378,467,392,418]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,239,473,497]" captionTargetBox="[167,1418,539,1286]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 2. Comparison among L. curvifurculus, sp. nov., L. bidentatus and L. viridus." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF16ABC4FFC8FFC9FF4245AA431895AB" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" tableUuid="DF16ABC4FFC8FFC9FF4245AA431895AB">
